%N A398012 Decimal expansion of -Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * log(k) / k^2, where lambda is Liouville's function (A008836).
%H A398012 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 379, Corollary 2.7.
%F A398012 Equals (Pi^2/15) * (log(2*Pi) + gamma + 12*log(A) + 240*log(A_3), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
